
Thread: a thread is a line of execution.

Thread class: the class available to create extra stacks(threads) in java that implements from Runnable interface.

Runnable Interface: the og functional interface for achieving multithreading.

run(): where we write the thread logic

start(): that internally calls run method based on thread scheduler.

currentThread(): gives details of current thread executing

sleep(): sends thread to waiting state till specified time.

join(): connects the execution of a thread to the main thread

stop(): stops a thread execution

interrupt(): stops a thread from executing in diff conditions

wait() ;sends thread to waiting state till notify is called

notify(): notifies a waiting thread to execute

notifyAll(): notifies all waiting threads to execute

setPriority(): sets priority of a thread

setDaemon(): makes a thread a background thread

isAlive(): checks is thread is active

synchronize keyword: acquires lock on the resource used by a thread


